ABSTRACT
A computer implemented method for detecting malicious
events occurring with respect to a blockchain data structure
comprising: defining a transaction creation profile according
to which transactions can be generated and submitted to the
blockchain; submitting a transaction to the blockchain, the
transaction causing the generation of a profiler data structure
in the blockchain including executable code to generate
profile transactions to be submitted to the blockchain
according to the transaction creation profile; monitoring the
blockchain to identify profile transactions; and comparing
identified profile transactions with the transaction creation
profile to detect a deviation from the transaction creation
profile, such detection corresponding to a malicious event
occurring with respect to the blockchain.
